The paper presents a new method of primate face recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and evaluates its performance on several endangered primate species. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of CNNs indicates that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The evaluation of the recognition system suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the implementation of an Android application suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
